description:
Comment SLAYGUIDE to get my free 30-page money guide.

Sometimes life choices feel so black and white. Either we‚Äôre spending money recklessly or we‚Äôre cutting back so much that it pains us to buy ourselves a new pair of shoes.‚Å†
‚Å†
But I‚Äôm telling you that both are dangerous and the longer it takes you to find the balance, the harder life will be.‚Å†
‚Å†
Frugality is usually an emotional response to money trauma.
‚Å†
Maybe you witnessed your parents or a family member struggling with money and now you hoard yours, because you don‚Äôt want to end up like they did.‚Å†
‚Å†
This means you may have lost some trust in yourself and your ability to make money throughout your life. I‚Äôve definitely experienced this. Even now I have moments where I fear that all the money I saved and invested will evaporate.‚Å†
‚Å†
Sounds crazy, right? But it‚Äôs a real fear that I struggle with and work to fight against.‚Å†
‚Å†
Whenever I spend money on anything luxurious, it‚Äôs a strike I take against this fear. That doesn‚Äôt mean I don‚Äôt regulate my spending. It just means that I intentionally choose what to spend extra money on and I practice doing so without feeling guilty or anxious.‚Å†
‚Å†
Investing definitely helped make me feel more secure.‚Å†
‚Å†
I know that I don‚Äôt have to be the one to create the money because the market is my partner. If I can‚Äôt make more, the market will make it for me. This has helped A LOT.‚Å†
‚Å†
So let‚Äôs get partnered up so you can take it easy. If you need a place to begin, comment SLAYGUIDE to get my free 30-page guide.

description:
I started investing when I was 28 which I thought was early until I met these kids on TikTok who have been investing since they were 18 üòÖ

Anyhoo, I‚Äôve learned a few lessons during this time:

‚úÖ There are no get rich quick schemes & a lot more ways to lose money. Investing works If you‚Äôre in it for the long term. Decades not weeks.

This is why I don‚Äôt day trade.

‚úÖ 401Ks & IRAs and all other retirement accounts are GREAT. They lower the tax burden today & tomorrow depending on which ones you choose & the funds offered in them have improved over time.

‚úÖ There are LEGAL tax loopholes for accessing these accounts early. 

‚úÖ Investing is simple but it‚Äôs not intuitive ‚Äî you need to learn how it works so you‚Äôre prepared for market downturns & staying on track with your investment plan.

description:
Comment FREEDOM below to join my free investing class!

Reposting this since it‚Äôs been a year since I moved to Portugal!

$17k for 2 years of health insurance is INSANE and I knew that. But having reliable health insurance when I needed is SO WORTH it to me.

PRO TIP: If you‚Äôre quitting a full time job to become self employed, do NOT take COBRA. You can‚Äôt deduct it as a business expense since it‚Äôs an employer-sponsored plan even though you‚Äôre paying in full. Just get your own policy directly from an insurance company or through the marketplace.

I definitely could‚Äôve gone with a cheaper insurance plan. An HMO would‚Äôve cost half.

But if I need a specialist I don‚Äôt want to be forced to go to an in-network doctor instead of the one I prefer. I don‚Äôt want to ask for a referral every time.

And last but definitely NOT LEAST, I can easily afford this cost. Most people cannot. And just because I can afford it doesn‚Äôt make it any less absurd.

I even had my gyno trying to tell me that I should cancel it and just pay her directly. Sounds nice while you‚Äôre healthy but not so great if you need life-saving surgery.

There‚Äôs a line between investing for the future and hoarding out of fear.

The skills you need to save, invest, and make money are not the same skills needed to spend your money.

Many people forget this.

Spending is a crucial step to living the life you dream of. But so many become fearful and can‚Äôt seem to let go of their frugal ways.

That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs important to understand your numbers. 

It‚Äôs important to know that if you spend X that you‚Äôre still on track to achieve Y.

Without this clarity it‚Äôs very easy for fear to seep in and for hoarding to become a way of life. 

And wouldn‚Äôt that be a shame?

description:
Comment FREEDOM below to join my free investing class!

Although I don‚Äôt believe that wealth makes you a certain way, I do think it amplifies who you are.

And if you come from a wealthy family that models selfish and unempathetic behavior then you will likely model that behavior as well.

Paul Piff and Dacher Keltner ran several studies looking at whether social class (as measured by wealth, occupational prestige, and education) influences how much we care about the feelings of others.

They found that ‚Äúless affluent individuals are more likely to report feeling compassion towards others on a regular basis.‚Äù

‚ÄúThese findings build upon previous research showing how upper-class individuals are worse at recognizing the emotions of others and less likely to pay attention to people they are interacting with.‚Äù

Why does wealth correlate with selfishness?

Piff and his colleagues suspect that the answer may have something to do with how wealth and abundance give us a sense of freedom and independence from others. The less we have to rely on others, the less we may care about their feelings. This leads us to be more self-focused. Another reason has to do with our attitudes towards greed. Like Gordon Gekko, upper-class people may be more likely to endorse the idea that ‚Äúgreed is good.‚Äù Piff and his colleagues found that wealthier people are more likely to agree with statements that greed is justified, beneficial, and morally defensible. These attitudes ended up predicting participants‚Äô likelihood of engaging in unethical behavior.‚Äù

Source: How Wealth Reduces Compassion, Scientific American

I share this not to say that we will all become selfish if we become wealthy. It‚Äôs to be more hyper-aware of this correlation so that you can catch yourself if you start losing perspective.

If anything, I‚Äôve become more hyper-aware of how others are suffering. I‚Äôve become more generous with my donating money and helping out family members.

However, I come from poverty. I know what it‚Äôs like to go without.

What if I had been born wealthy?

It‚Äôs not a black-and-white issue but one we should all be aware of.

Why do I talk about being child free?

Because women should not be valued based on their reproductive choices or capacity. 

No one ever attacks a man‚Äôs credibility or competence for being child free. 

44% of adult, child-free Americans aged 18-49 say it is not too likely or not at all likely they will become parents in the future. 

You think these issues aren‚Äôt connected to finance? Has nothing to do with investing?

Single child-free women out earn single child-free men. 

The rising cost of living, lack of paid parental leave, daycare costs, and retirement prospects have all contributed to these decisions. 

Besides all of these hurdles, some of us simply CHOOSE not to be parents for no other reason than we don‚Äôt want to be. And that‚Äôs ok. 

Child free women are still valuable. 

Many are caretakers & community builders. 

Many are accomplished professionals. 

Many are living ordinary lives just like many child free men who don‚Äôt get harassed about it. 

Oh and Harris has two step children. She is a mother & a provider. 

The patriarchy is shooook.

Had a fabulous day all on my own today and no social hangover üòÖ I know my introverts understand.

It helps that it‚Äôs summer in Lisbon and I‚Äôm surrounded by gorgeous rooftops. üòç

Someone asked how I‚Äôm able to be comfortable at a restaurant on my own and it did take some getting used to. I suggest listening to a podcast or audio book at first. You‚Äôll feel less awkward. But eventually you should work towards being totally immersed in the moment so that you can really experience everything around you.

I find that meals that I have alone are much more memorable because I‚Äôm not distracted with conversation. I also tend to drink a lot less on my own than when I‚Äôm around people because I‚Äôm not trying to manage my social anxiety with alcohol.

Give it a try! And this goes for my single pringles and coupled baddies. Solo time away from a partner is important too especially if you‚Äôre an introvert.

description:
Comment FREEDOM below to join my free investing class!

Have I had bad experiences with employers? Hell yeah. I‚Äôve had 3 professional jobs from 2001-2021 (one before law school & two as an attorney) & all 3 had massive toxic traits. But I don‚Äôt base this video on that experience. I base it on 14 years of experience as an employment attorney where I represented employees & studied countless cases. I‚Äôve lost count of how many case holdings I‚Äôve read.

These records are all public & anyone can access them. You can google it. In addition to public records, I also saw all the confidential agreements & arbitrations of the cases I worked on which are not public & I cannot discuss.

Many people think I was only speaking from personal experience when in fact, this is the nature of most workplaces in America. Are there exceptions? Of course there are.

Regardless of whether you agree or disagree with my sentiments, I hope you take away the lesson that we should all be building an FU Fund. I first heard this term from JL Collins, the author of a Simple Path to Wealth.

Why? Because financial independence is something we should all strive for to help build security & stability in good times & especially in bad times. If the last 2 years hasn‚Äôt taught us that I don‚Äôt know what will. I wouldn‚Äôt bank on an employer‚Äôs good graces as my safety net.

That doesn‚Äôt mean you can‚Äôt be friendly at work. Of course you can & you should! But not every colleague deserves your trust & the details about your private life. Use your judgement & be really picky about who you confide in.

DO NOT ever think that HR is your friend. They‚Äôre there to represent the company, PERIOD. Many HR managers agreed in the comments of this video so keep that in mind.

FU Fund means saying FU to anything or anyone that steals your peace & all it takes is one new manager or coworker to ruin a perfectly fine work environment. Don‚Äôt ever get so comfortable you forget to CYA because I GUARANTEE you your boss & your company is doing just that.

‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#corporateamerica #corporatelife #debtfreejourney #investing101 #financetips #personalfinances #financialliteracy #financialindependencejourney #moneymanagement

description:

Anyway, instead of judging me you should instead be asking questions like:

‚ÄúHow much of your income are you spending on rent?‚Äù

It‚Äôs about 15%-20% of my monthly income 

‚ÄúAre you still able to stay on track for your financial independence goal?‚Äù 

Absolutely. I waited at least 3 years before upgrading my lifestyle when I started earning more so that I could get ahead. 

Thanks to that I can spend more now stress free knowing that I‚Äôm set for retirement by 45. 

I have a net worth of $1.9M & I‚Äôm debt free. 

Until three years ago I had only lived in small cramped studio apartments. This is my time to enjoy the fruits of my labor. 

Context matters y‚Äôall. 

I‚Äôm living my dream life. I want you to live yours even if it‚Äôs completely different from mine.

How much time you spend working at your job and at home. Take your salary and divide it by all those hours. That‚Äôs your true hourly wage because if you were to outsource those tasks, you‚Äôd have to pay someone to do them.

Somehow women have been convinced that household chores is not work and yet most men don‚Äôt want to do it. If it‚Äôs so easy then you load the dishwasher Chad!

I know it‚Äôs easier sometimes to ‚Äújust do it yourself‚Äù but it‚Äôs really not. It‚Äôs not your job to be someone‚Äôs maid or someone‚Äôs cook.

There are no masculine or feminine chores. There are just chores and guess what? When you‚Äôre single, you do them all! So why are we dividing it by gender when we have a partner? Because patriarchy has brainwashed us into thinking this way.

Women initiate 70% of divorces because we are TIRED. We are tired of having to do it all. Our job, house manager, emotional regulator, etc.

We don‚Äôt like doing dishes either. We don‚Äôt like cooking either. But yes we do want a clean home and we‚Äôre not going to live in our own filth. So we just do it but that will get old and she will get over having to do twice the cleaning and cooking for no reason.

I don‚Äôt take any of it for granted nor do I ignore the fact that I‚Äôm extremely lucky to be in this position.
